						<summary>

						<p>This inscription which is very much damaged and mutilated appears to belong to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Bhuvanaikmalladēva (Sōmēśvara II)</hi> and to be dated in <hi rend="bold">Śaka 996, Rākshasa, Pushya, śu • • • • •</hi> (= A.D. 1075—1076). Reference is made to the <hi rend="bold">Beḷvala</hi> country and its <hi rend="italic">rājadhānī</hi> <hi rend="bold">Aṇṇi[geṟe]</hi> and to an <hi rend="italic">agrahāra</hi> in the <hi rend="bold">Māsavāḍi</hi> division. Details of <hi rend="bold">date</hi> are not enough for calculation.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
